The paper focuses on generative reading comprehension and natural language generation, which are topics related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a multi-style abstractive summarization model, which involves learning multi-style answers within a model, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates its model's performance on the Q&A task and the Q&A + NLG task of MS MARCO 2.1, which are information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks. Finally, the paper discusses the transfer of the style-independent NLG capability to the target style, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
